<TEXT>
meat from half a million new zealand 
sheep ritually slaughtered during this years moslem pilgrimage 
will be distributed to poor moslems in 24 countries a senior 
official said 
ahmed mohammed ali president of the islamic development bank 
which oversees the sacrificial meat utilization program said 
thursday that the operation will cost 37 million 
the project a joint venture between the government and 
45member islamic development bank was started in 1983 to make 
use of the meat that was otherwise left to rot in the desert 
that year only 63000 sheep were slaughtered to mark the climax 
of the monthlong pilgrimage to islams holiest sites at mecca and 
medina the meat was sent to three countries 
the slaughter commemorates the willingness of the prophet 
abraham to sacrifice his son for god 
