of german unification or through a treaty being negotiated between 
nato and the warsaw pact in vienna so will a lot of tanks and 
artillery pieces 
the question facing bush prime minister margaret thatcher of 
britain president francois mitterrand of france and the other 
allied leaders is whether to revise nato doctrine and remove or at 
least play down the nuclear threat 
as for nato strategy it obviously no longer makes sense to make 
plans to defend a border between east and west germany that will 
soon disappear 
but those are the kinds of tough questions that will take a long 
time to answer right now celebration is the order of the day 
