job was published in the review called the decision 
symptomatic of what is happening in publishing where money has 
become more important than words 
yale president benno c schmidt jr announced thursday that the 
review will cease after the issues in progress go to print he 
cited the magazines deficits that the university must absorb its 
limited readership and the absence of any direct tie to yales 
academic programs 
the time has come either to make significant changes in the 
magazine or to discontinue its publication in a dignified way 
schmidt said i have chosen to do the latter 
the review began in 1819 as the christian spectator and became 
the yale review in 1911 it is considered the grandparent of other 
literary journals including the kenyon georgia southern and 
suwannee reviews 
over the years the magazine has showcased a blend of criticism 
essays poetry and fiction by known and emerging writers 
