a french company announced plans friday to launch 
the soviet unions first instant lottery hoping the lure of 
big prizes will sell hundreds of millions of tickets for the 
benefit of a charity group 
the lottery is scheduled to begin by the end of july with an 
initial distribution of 200 million tickets said georgesrobert 
parisot president of the international section of the societe 
internationale des jeux the company that runs the french national 
lottery 
he said the tickets are to be sold in the soviet union by the 
soviet childrens fund which was established several years ago to 
look after the interests of children the fund is officially 
independent but has close ties to the government 
parisot told the associated press the biggest prizes in the 
instant lottery would be 25000 rubles equivalent to 42000 at 
the standard exchange rate or 4200 at the tourist exchange rate 
he said the tickets will sell for five rubles apiece 830 at 
the standard rate or 83 cents at the tourist rate 
although the first order is for 200 million tickets parisot 
said he expected billions would be sold in the soviet union which 
has a population of almost 300 million he said 57 percent of 
ticket sale proceeds would be paid back in prizes with the 
remainder going to the childrens fund and administrative costs 
the french company which will print the tickets and run the 
lottery will keep a percentage of the administrative costs 
there has been a longstanding lottery in the soviet union but 
the best prizes are often appliances or infrequently 
automobiles 
an accord signed by parisot and an official of the soviet 
childrens fund proposed the creation of a joint frenchsoviet 
company by march 1991 to expand lottery operations in the soviet 
union and to establish a facility for printing lottery tickets in 
the soviet union by 1993 
in an instant lottery a participant learns immediately whether 
he or she is a winner by scratching away a covering over part of 
the ticket in traditional lotteries the ticket purchaser must 
await some sort of drawing to determine if he or she has the lucky 
number 
