daredevil rides continue to draw summer crowds america it seems 
is undergoing a roller coaster renaissance 
whats happening is rides in general and coasters in 
particular are getting bigger faster wilder and yet safer than 
ever before says paul ruben editor of rollercoaster magazine 
i think everyone seeks adventure ruben says a great 
roller coaster ride will make your heart pound your adrenalin 
pump it will make you feel alive 
some summer pleasures remain simple that most hallowed of 
summer pastimes baseball still fascinates americans little boys 
and girls still sign up for little league and their parents still 
play for softball teams sponsored by local businesses 
