games are good marsden says 
sporting goods and camping equipment continue to sell briskly 
americans snapped up more than 44 billion in sports gear last 
year says glenn bischoff a spokesman for the national sporting 
goods association in chicago 
but the implements of fitness like everything else have grown 
more complicated than a wooden louisville slugger 
ten years ago you had barbells and stationary bikes says 
bischoff now you have stairclimbers treadmills and rowing 
machines people are always willing to pay for more bells and 
whistles 
americans marsden observes want to tie up their summer 
recreation with hightech gadgets fun thats too simple might not 
be so much fun he says 
tennis become popularized and accessible and then no one 
wanted to play marsden says now weve got bigger rackets 
complex alloys its become fancier and more costly so now people 
want to play again 
the next hightech summer thrills gadget may lie literally on 
the horizon 
para gliding a cheaper and simpler version of hang gliding is 
just sailing into this country from europe 
for about 2000 an enthusiast can purchase a pack that 
contains a sophisticated nylon parachute that billows out into a 
wing when filled with wind put simply the user dons the pack 
runs downhill and into the wind and becomes airborne 
this says peter zimmerli president of the american para 
gliding association is going to be big 
