<TEXT>
here is a statistical sketch of the 198990 
supreme court term 
the 129 signed decisions are the fewest since the 198081 term 
when there were 123 some terms in between produced more than 150 
justice byron r white was the courts voice more often than 
any other member he wrote 17 majority opinions 
justice john paul stevens wrote the most opinions 55 that 
includes majority concurring and dissenting opinions chief 
justice william h rehnquist wrote the fewest 21 
the chief justice who believes most court decisions are too 
long and include too many separate views authored 15 majority 
opinions two dissents and four concurring opinions he otherwise 
was content to join someone elses opinion 
justice thurgood marshall was the most prolific dissenter with 
50 such votes 
white dissented the fewest times 11 
there were 37 cases decided by 54 votes compared with 32 the 
previous term seventeen of the 54 votes were announced in june 
</TEXT>
