claris which develops and markets software for apples popular 
macintosh and apple ii computers has been a majorityowned 
subsidiary of apple since april 1987 when apple spun off its 
applications software operations to form claris 
at the time apple said it retained the option to turn claris 
into a publicly owned company or to return the subsidiary to full 
apple ownership 
software will increasingly become the factor which shapes 
competitive advantage in the 1990s said sculley who also serves 
as apples chief executive officer with that in mind we have 
established a new expanded role for claris which will become an 
important foundation for apple in the future 
sculley said claris will focus on three main areas 
continued development and marketing of its applications 
software 
development and marketing of extensions to apples system 
software which controls a computers basic operations such as 
responding to keyboard commands and organizing files 
development and marketing of products that link macintosh with 
other computing environments 
claris will remain independent and maintain separate facilities 
and personnel william v campbell ceo of claris will report to 
sculley 
