<TEXT>
atlantic richfield co said friday it had 
paid 800 million to the internal revenue service to settle a 
dispute over windfall profit taxes on alaska oil lifting a 
longstanding cloud over the company 
the payment settles a claim for back taxes and interest that 
totaled 18 billion believed to be the largest claim ever 
presented to a company by the irs in settling the dispute arco 
admitted no wrongdoing 
arco the secondbiggest producer of alaska crude oil said the 
payment will resolve all irs claims for additional windfall profit 
taxes including interest on its north slope production from 1980 
to 1985 
arco had set aside reserves since the mid1980s to cover 
settlements of disputes over alaska oil it said those reserves 
covered the huge payment 
