<TEXT>
jury deliberations began friday in the 
conspiracy and fraud case against john a mulheren jr the former 
stock speculator accused of engaging in sham securities 
transactions with ivan boesky 
the panel of eight women and four men deliberated for several 
hours after receiving legal instructions from us district judge 
miriam goldman cederbaum the jury is to resume its deliberations 
on monday 
mulheren 41 of rumson nj is charged with 30 counts of 
conspiracy stock manipulation securities fraud mail fraud and 
recordkeeping violations in connection with a series of 
transactions with boesky in 1985 and 1986 
also named is leonard l destefano 34 a former trader at 
mulherens nowdefunct jamie securities co destefano is charged 
with one count each of conspiracy and violating federal 
recordkeeping statutes 
the case included the first public testimony by boesky the 
former speculator who settled insider trading charges with the 
government in 1986 by agreeing to plead guilty to one felony and 
pay 100 million in penalties 
boesky was required to cooperate with the government in its 
investigation of wall street fraud he was released from federal 
custody in april after completing two years of a threeyear prison 
term 
mulheren is accused of manipulating the price of gulf amp western 
inc stock by buying large blocks to help aid boesky who wanted to 
sell a large stake in the company he acquired 
he also is charged with temporarily holding other securities for 
boesky to help boesky evade taxes and federal securities laws 
concealing the ownership of securities also known as parking 
with the intent to deceive is illegal under federal law 
the trial is in its seventh week in us district court in 
manhattan 
</TEXT>
