<TEXT>
time warner inc sued pathe communications 
corp for 100 million friday contending pathe broke a contract 
giving time warner inc distribution rights to pathe and united 
artists films 
the lawsuit was the latest development in the struggle by 
giancarlo parretti the italian financier who owns pathe to finnce 
his proposed 13 billion buyout of mgmua communications co 
time warner agreed april 9 to lend pathe 650 million toward the 
purchase in return for distribution rights to new pathe and united 
artists films and the valuable united artists movie library time 
warner also got a lien on the library as collateral 
but time warner insisted that pathe provide the rest in equity 
at least 450 million of that from pathes own sources rather than 
borrowed money 
pathe had been trying to renegotiate the equity part of the 
deal but announced thursday it had reached an impasse with time 
warner pathe said it would continue to talk with time warner but 
also would seek alternate sources of financing 
time warners lawsuit filed in los angeles superior court 
alleges that pathe acted as if the contract gave pathe a oneway 
option to decide which of its obligations it would honor which 
time warner rights it could ignore and which conditions it would 
satisfy 
pathe spokesman craig parsons said no one at beverly hillsbased 
pathe had seen the lawsuit and thus could not comment on it 
asked if it was a surprise he said things had not in our 
view gotten that hostile so im at a loss to explain it at this 
point 
the lawsuit asserts that pathe is creating a smokescreen to 
obscure the actual fact that pathe was unable or unwilling to 
perform under the april 9 letter agreement and as an excuse to seek 
alternative financing 
mgmuas stock price fell friday on the news that the main 
source of financing for pathes offer was in jeopardy 
the stock which fell 62 cents per share to 1725 on the new 
york stock exchange already was trading far below the level 
expected if investors believed pathes 2150pershare offer would 
be completed as scheduled on oct 23 analysts said 
under parrettis latest agreement with kirk kerkorian the 
billionaire who controls mgmua 4 per share of the 2150 is to 
be paid to mgmua shareholders on july 20 
parretti already has put 200 million into escrow which will be 
used toward the distribution he is to kick in another 53 million 
to get to the 4pershare level 
many of those buying mgmua stock dont believe the deal will go 
through said jeffrey logsdon an analyst with crowell weedon inc 
in los angeles 
instead he said theyre gambling that they can pocket the 4 
then get the rest of their money back and more when kerkorian sells 
the studio to another buyer at a lower price 
pathe spokesman parsons noted that the company already has the 
200 million in cash down payments invested in the deal he said 
the company was looking at a broad universe of options for 
raising the rest of the money 
the lawsuit filed friday by time warner inc and time warner 
home video inc accuses pathe of breaching theatrical and home 
video distribution agreements for pathe films with respect to the 
video rights agreement the lawsuit says pathe entered into the 
agreement without telling warner it already had previously granted 
the rights to another company 
</TEXT>
